# WAI-Harness — always-clean invariant
#
# The tree is clean BY CONSTRUCTION:
#   managed/  — tracked + MANIFEST-verified; changes ONLY via a verified upgrade.
#   */local/  — every runtime-writable artifact the harness produces (sessions,
#               runtime state, buffers, db, savepoints, bolts, kpi, …). Gitignored
#               so no operation can ever dirty the tracked tree. Skeleton dirs are
#               kept (.gitkeep) so the structure exists on a fresh checkout.
#
# If a future write lands OUTSIDE local/ and dirties the tree, that is a bug in the
# writer (it should target local/), not a reason to widen this ignore.

spoke/local/**
hub/local/**
!spoke/local/**/
!hub/local/**/
!**/.gitkeep

# build / runtime artifacts (never source, non-deterministic)
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
**/.pytest_cache/
**/.DS_Store
